info.senderName: NWS LaCrosse (Southwestern Wisconsin, Southeastern Minnesota, and Northeast Iowa)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued May 05 at 9:56AM CDT until May 07 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS LaCrosse
info.description: ...Observed flooding changed from Minor to Major severity and increased in duration for the following rivers in Minnesota... Wisconsin... Mississippi River at Winona affecting Buffalo, Trempealeau and Winona Counties. ...Observed flooding changed from Minor to Major severity for the following rivers in Minnesota...Wisconsin... Mississippi River at La Crosse affecting La Crosse, Vernon and Houston Counties. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL EARLY SUNDAY AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Mississippi River at Winona. * WHEN...Until early Sunday afternoon. * IMPACTS...At 13.0 feet, Prairie Island Park begins to flood. Pumping operations are underway by the city of Winona, and dike patrols are started. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 8:45 AM CDT Friday the stage was 13.9 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 8:45 AM CDT Friday was 14.4 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage Sunday morning and continue falling to 11.1 feet Friday morning. - Flood stage is 13.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Additional river and weather information is available at www.weather.gov/lacrosse. The next statement will be issued this evening by 1100 PM CDT.
